---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = 'About us';
const pageDescription = 'Learn more about the Bardic project';
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} lang="en">
  <Header currentLang="en" />
  <main class="flex-1 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-secondary-900 mb-8">About us</h1>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">Aim of the website</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary-700 mb-6">
          Gorsedd is a comprehensive database of individuals who have been admitted to the Gorsedd at the National Eisteddfod of Wales. Gorsedd is a 'Beta' website for researchers, students and members of the public interested in the history of the Eisteddfod and Welsh culture.        
        </p>
        <p>
          This dataset was compiled from items in the National Library of Wales collections and recorded by volunteers as part of the <a href="https://www.library.wales/about-nlw/work-with-us/volunteer" class="font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline">National Library of Wales Volunteering Programme.</a> We would like to extend our sincere thanks to our four volunteers, Nonna, Christine, Ian, and especially Owen Watkin for their dedication and valuable contributions to this project.
        </p>
        <br />
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">What information is available?</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary-700 mb-6">
          The website contains information about bardic names, locations, type of membership, and their contribution to Welsh culture. The data has been collected from reliable historical sources by volunteers at the National Library of Wales.
          <br />Note: Not all profiles are complete, it depends on the information available to the volunteers.
        </p>    
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">How to Use the Website</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-secondary-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Use the search box on the home page to find a specific individual</li>
          <li>Browse through the grid of individuals' cards to discover information</li>
          <li>Click on individual to see full details</li>
          <li>Download the full data from the download page</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary-700">
          If you have questions or would like to contribute to the project, please feel free to <a href="https://www.library.wales/index.php?id=12960" class="font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline">contact us.</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <Footer currentLang="en" />
</Layout>